<h1>Frostreaver</h1>
	Haldraeger-oop wrote (about Frostreaver):<P>&lt;Item statistics cut&gt;<P><B>Class: WAR PAL SHD<BR>Race: HUM BAR DWF TRL OGR IKS<P>==================================================<P>Can anyone tell me why  a High Elf, Half Elf, Erudite, Dark Elf, Wood elf, Halfling, Vah Sir can't use this Axe?  Why isn't it  ALL/ALL?<P>From a roleplaying perspective why would a Dwarf take an axe from an brethren Dwarf?</B><P>Elves, Erudites and Halflings don't have the mass to wield the axe.  Only the bulkier races can use it.<P>I have no idea why a Dwarf would take an axe from a Coldain.  I certainly can't see why a Dwarf would want to kill one to take his stuff.  But that doesn't mean that a Dwarf would be physically unable to use an axe built specifically for use by the Coldain.  And I'm sure there are some folks out there playing Dwarves that <I>do</I> have a reason to take the axe, the hard way if needed.<P>"It's a trick, get the axe."  poorly quoted - Ash<P>Alan<BR>

<hr>

Gil-galor wrote:<P><B>Your "bulk" explanation explains why the smaller to medium sized races can't use the axe but it doesn't explain why the Vah Shir(sp?) can't use it.</B><P>I'd be inclined to call the Vah Shir tall and lithe rather than bulky.  Considering they do not have the Slam ability (as far as I can recall) that other big races have, I'd say that they aren't bulky enough.<P>Alan<BR>



